<section id="Overview">
  <div id="slides">
    <ul class="slides-container">
      <li>
	<h2>A-B testing.</h2>
	<ul>
	  <li>One created, every generation of a nix environment is cached
	    until removed.</li>
	  <li>You can trivially switch between each generation.</li>
	  <li>The environments will share everything that is shareable and run
	    on the same host, minimizing your test variables.</li>
	</ul>
      </li>
      <!-- I really want to do do:

	   <li id="Agument-build-systems">

	   It kind of works and you can even link to it and it'll show
	   up, but it messes up the 'next' arrow behavior for some
	   reason. -->
      <li>
	<h2>Augment build systems.</h2>
	<div class="p">
	  <ul>
	    <li>Nix is an easy way to add technology agnostic dependency
	      management.</li>
	    <li>Can use same system to build from local development
	      checkous.</li>
	    <li>Integrates remote caching to speed up setting up the second
	      and third builds.</li>
	    <li>Can quickly rollbacak to previous environment states.</li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
      </li>
      <li>
	<h2>Organize micro-distributions.</h2>
	<div class="p">
	  Define 'distro' nix expression for a group of applications
	  and their stack.
	  <ul>
	    <li>Easily provision hosts and workstations.</li>
	    <li>Clearly defines both product and stack elements.</li>
	    <li>In some cases, is useful in public product distribution;
	      especially with open source projects.</li>
	  </ul>
	</div>
      </li>
    </ul>
